  "text": "Once a genome sequence has been determined, an immediate task is to identify all the genes. Arguably, the best way to do this is by sequence similarity. Indeed, if a putative protein encoded by an uncharacterized ORF shows statistically significant similarity to another protein of known The phylogenetic distribution of bacterial species that are the subjects of genome-sequencing projects. The tree topology, based on 16 S rRNA sequences, is from [CITATION_1] . The solid lines indicate lineages that include archaea (red) and bacteria (green) whose genomes are being sequenced. Major branches that are not represented in genomesequencing projects are shown by broken lines.",
